  "uuid": "6cc5af0fc0e20cb04cd6b9adf9e28f2d",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Regulatory Affairs Specialist",
  "description": "<p>You will play a critical role in ensuring that the company’s products, operations, and processes comply with applicable regulatory requirements across multiple markets. Reporting directly to the General Manager, you will work closely with cross-functional teams to manage regulatory compliance, monitor regulatory changes, and support continuous improvement initiatives.</p><p><u>Candidate Requirements</u></p><p><u>Education</u></p><p>Bachelor’s degree or above in Regulatory Affairs, Chemistry, Life Sciences, Pharmaceutical Sciences, Biomedical Sciences, or related disciplines</p><p><u>Experience</u></p><p>Minimum 3–8 years of hands-on experience in Regulatory Affairs, Product Compliance, or related regulatory functions</p><p>Proven experience in product registration, notification, or regulatory dossier preparation</p><p>Experience in cleaning products, chemical products, disinfectants, cosmetics, or medical/healthcare products preferred</p><p>Prior exposure to ASEAN, EU, or US regulatory markets is strongly preferred</p><p><u>Regulatory & Technical Knowledge</u></p><p>Solid understanding of regional and international regulations (ASEAN / EU / US)</p><p>Familiar with SDS, ingredient compliance, REACH, SVHC, labeling and claims requirements</p><p>Experience preparing and maintaining Technical Files, Product Information Files (PIF), or regulatory dossiers</p><p>Knowledge of GMP/ISO documentation systems</p><p>Experience supporting customer or regulatory audits is a plus</p><p><u>Core Competencies</u></p><p>Strong documentation and attention to detail</p><p>Ability to interpret regulations and translate them into practical business actions</p><p>Independent, proactive, and solution-oriented mindset</p><p>Strong project management and multitasking capability</p><p>Comfortable working across multiple countries and regulatory frameworks</p><p>Effective communication and stakeholder management skills</p><p><u>Language Skills</u></p><p>Fluent in English (written and spoken)</p><p>Mandarin is a plus for collaboration with regional teams</p><p><u>Preferred Qualifications</u></p><p>Experience with medical devices or disinfectant/biocide products</p><p>Hands-on experience with HSA, FDA, EU submissions or notifications</p><p>ESG or supply chain compliance knowledge</p><p>Experience building regulatory systems or processes from the ground up</p>",
